<p style="text-align:center;font-style:italic;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:1.15rem">Microgreens harvested the morning of service, delivered direct from the grower. No distributor, no broker, no week-old produce.</p>

<p class="cta-row"><a href="#contact"><strong>Talk to us about wholesale →</strong></a></p>

<h2>Why chefs use us</h2>

<p><strong>Cut the morning of service.</strong> Most distributors run produce through three stops before it reaches your back door. By the time you're plating, it's a week old. We harvest the morning we deliver. Period.</p>

<p><strong>Consistent supply, custom volume.</strong> Tell us what you need on what days. We seed for it. You get the same yield every week without surprise outages.</p>

<p><strong>Direct chef-to-grower line.</strong> Want to try a variety we don't list? Want longer pea tendrils for a specific dish? Want a particular harvest stage? Text us. No account manager, no procurement portal. You talk to the family that grew it.</p>

<p><strong>Visual quality.</strong> Our chard, beet, and radish are cut for the stem color, not just for yield. Plate-ready.</p>

<h2>What we grow</h2>

<p>Ten varieties, organic non-GMO seeds, filtered water, sanitized trays. Each variety is available with consistent flavor and yield week over week.</p>

