<h2>Wholesale pricing</h2>

<p>Wholesale rates apply at standing weekly volumes starting at <strong>1 lb per week per variety</strong> (about 16oz, or four standard restaurant clamshells). We price by volume, by variety, and by harvest stage. Message us with your weekly need and we'll quote.</p>

<h2>Delivery schedule</h2>

<p>We can match almost any kitchen's prep schedule. Our current routes hit Winter Park, College Park, Maitland, downtown Orlando, and the Seminole County suburbs. If you're in greater Orlando and we don't already drive past you, we'll build the stop in.</p>

<h2>Common questions from chefs</h2>

<details><summary>What is the minimum wholesale order?</summary><p>One pound per week per variety, about 16 ounces or four standard restaurant clamshells. Below that, retail pricing applies.</p></details>

<details><summary>Can you grow a variety not on the menu?</summary><p>Often yes. Tell us the cultivar, the harvest stage, and your weekly need. If the seed is available from our suppliers and the grow window fits the route, we will trial it.</p></details>

<details><summary>How does invoicing work?</summary><p>We invoice weekly via email. Payment via ACH, Venmo, Zelle, or check. Net 7 standard, longer terms available for established accounts.</p></details>

<details><summary>Can I see and taste a sample before committing?</summary><p>Yes. Reach out via the form below, tell us which restaurant you cook at, and we will hand-deliver a small sample of the varieties you are curious about on the next route through your area.</p></details>

<details><summary>How much notice do you need for a new variety or volume change?</summary><p>Two weeks to seed a brand new variety. One week to scale an existing variety up or down. Same-week one-offs are usually possible for small additions to an existing standing order.</p></details>

